I really enjoyed the pilot, and also last night's episode. I thought the girl in it was perfectly cast. She was kind of weird looking but also very pretty but also really odd. Mangan is excellent and a lot of the physical humour they've added is really entertaining. A lot of book conversions forget that this is important for television, but they've done a great job with it. It definitely serves as a perfect silly counterpoint to the new Sherlock Holmes series.
