Posted: Tue Mar 13, 2012 12:33 pm
Hinton's not completely wrong, the last few episodes of the first Hitch Hiker's series were written with the assistance of John Lloyd because Adams could not meet a deadline to save his life (Apparently Geoffrey Perkins also helped.) However the books omit a lot of the stuff that was not written by Adams. This is detailed in Neil Gaiman's book "Don't panic: the official hitch hiker's guide to the galaxy companion". Lloyd must not have minded (or got over it) because they wrote "the Meaning of liff" together later.
